PyEZ unit test execution :
nose tests:

python3.9 -m pip install nose
python3.9 -m pip install mock
python3.9 -m pip install coverage
python3.9 -m pip install ntc_templates

cd /root/pyez/py-junos-eznc/tests/unit

nosetests -v *

pip install ntc-templates
pip install textfsm


To run the pyez unit tests :

cd py-junos-eznc/tests/unit
nosetests -v --with-coverage --cover-package=jnpr.junos --cover-inclusive -a unit


To run jsnapy unit tests
cd tests/unit
nosetests -v --with-coverage --cover-package=jnpr.jsnapy --cover-inclusive -a unit


To check compilation errors
find . -iname '*.py' | xargs -P4 -I{} python3.7 -Wall -m py_compile {}

To run functional tests

nosetests -v --with-xunit --xunit-file=functionaltests.xml --with-coverage --cover-package=jnpr.junos --cover-xml --cover-inclusive --cover-erase test_utils_file_system.py test_config.py test_core.py test_exception.py test_file_ftp.py test_file_scp.py test_route_table.py test_rpc.py test_route_table.py test_shell.py test_table_present.py test_telnet.py test_utils_file_system.py test_utils_sw.py


nosetests -v --with-xunit --xunit-file=functionaltests.xml --with-coverage --cover-package=jnpr.junos --cover-xml --cover-inclusive --cover-erase test_utils_file_system



